\par 
\par Blessed are the poor in spirit,/ for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par 
\par Blessed are they that mourn,/ for they shall be comforted.
\par 
\par Blessed are the meek,/ for they shall inherit the earth.
\par 
\par Blessed are they that hunger and thirst after righteousness,/ for they shall be filled.
\par      
\par Blessed are the merciful,/ for they shall obtain mercy.
\par 
\par Blessed are the pure in heart,/ for they shall see God.
\par 
\par Blessed are the peacemakers,/ for they shall be called sons of God.
\par 
\par Blessed are they that are persecuted for righteousness' sake,/ for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
\par 
\par Blessed are ye when men shall revile you and persecute you,/ and shall say all manner of evil against you falsely for My sake.
\par 
\par Rejoice and be exceeding glad,/ for great is your reward in the heavens.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father,/ and to the Son,/ and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever,/ and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
