 is good; blessed is the man that hopeth in Him. \line O fear the Lord, all ye His saints; for there is no want to them that fear Him. \line Rich men have turned poor and gone hungry; but they that seek the Lord shall not be deprived of any good thing. 
\line Come ye children, hearken unto me; I will teach you the fear of the Lord. \line What man is there that desireth life, who loveth to see good days? \line Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile. \line 
Turn away from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it. \line The eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and His ears are opened unto their supplication. \line 
The face of the Lord is against them that do evil, utterly to destroy the remembrance of them from the earth. \line The righteous cried, and the Lord heard them, and He delivered them out of all their tribulations. \line 
The Lord is nigh unto them that are of a contrite heart, and He will save the humble of spirit. \line Many are the tribulations of the righteous, and the Lord shall deliver them out of them all. \line The Lord keepeth
